cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with distributed algorithms for data summarization, which is a topic in distributed computing and graph algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI) due to its focus on communication graphs and mixing time. Finally, the paper discusses the GOSSIP model, which is a type of social network model, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category as well.
